.TH "bee-install" "1" "2011-08-11" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee package management"
.SH "NAME"
bee\-install \- Install a bee package
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee install"
.OP \-afhuv
.OP \-\-noop
.I bee-package
.YS
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee-install
is used to install a bee package.
.P
Normally
.B bee-install
searches
.B BEE_PKGDIR
for
.I bee-package
but you can use
.BI /path/to/ bee-package .bee.tar.bz2
too.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-a
.TQ
.B \-\-all
.TQ
.B \-v
.TQ
.B \-\-verbose
Run
.B bee-install
in verbose mode.
.TP
.B \-f
.TQ
.B \-\-force
Use
.B \-f
to prevent
.B bee-install
from checking whether
.I bee-package
is already installed.
.TP
.B \-h
.TQ
.B \-\-help
Print a little help screen.
.TP
.B \-u
.TQ
.B \-\-update
Install
.I bee\-package
and remove all other installed versions of this package.
Downgrades are possible by forcing the installation of lower versions with the
.B \-f
option.
.TP
.B \-\-noop
Run bee in noop mode.
.SH "FILES"
.TP
.B /etc/bee/beerc
.TQ
.B ~/.beerc
The main config files. Use these to change
.BR bee-install 's
environment variables.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_PKGDIR
.RS
Directory searched for available bee packages
.P
Defaults:
.TQ
root-user: /usr/src/bee/packages
.TQ
other:     ~/.local/src/bee/packages
.RE
.\" .SH "BUGS"
